# tinyproxy FilterDefaultDeny allowlist for the review container.
#
# These are extended regex (anchored implicitly by tinyproxy); only CONNECT
# host matches are checked (ConnectPort 443 in tinyproxy.conf restricts
# to HTTPS). Anything not matched here is denied with a 403.
#
# Rebuild the egress-proxy image and recreate its container whenever these
# change (or if Anthropic/GitHub introduce new subdomains).

# --- GitHub ---------------------------------------------------------------
# api.github.com — REST API for `gh` repo/pr queries.
# codeload.github.com — tarball/zip downloads, some gh flows.
# uploads.github.com — used by gh for some read paths; harmless read-only.
# raw.githubusercontent.com — raw file fetches by gh.
# objects.githubusercontent.com — release assets.
^api\.github\.com$
^codeload\.github\.com$
^uploads\.github\.com$
^raw\.githubusercontent\.com$
^objects\.githubusercontent\.com$
# Catch-all for any other *.github.com subdomain gh may touch.
^[a-z0-9-]+\.github\.com$

# --- Anthropic ------------------------------------------------------------
# Claude Code CLI contacts api.anthropic.com for completions.
^api\.anthropic\.com$
^[a-z0-9-]+\.anthropic\.com$

# NOTE: Postgres (DigitalOcean managed DB host) is NOT here. libpq bypasses
# HTTP_PROXY entirely; Postgres traffic goes through the db-tunnel sidecar
# on its own connection. See db-tunnel.Dockerfile.
